<section id="command-macroexpand">
    <title>MACROEXPAND</title>
<indexterm><primary>MACROEXPAND</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>MACROEXPAND</command> <parameter>macrocall</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Operation that inputs &GENERICNAME; expression (<parameter>macrocall</parameter>) that invokes a macro and outputs the &GENERICNAME; expression into which the macro would translate the input expression.
</para>

<para>
The <parameter>macrocall</parameter> input must be a list that begins with the name of a macro.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>


<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW MACROEXPAND [LOCALMAKE "pi 3.14159]</userinput>
[local "pi apply "make [pi 3.14159]]
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
